  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the remaining</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Mix the<strong> lean</strong> <strong>pork mixture</strong> thoroughly until fully combined, then shape into 3 patties per person (they don't have to look perfect)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until browned on both sides and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze the juice of<strong> half </strong>your <strong>lime[s]</strong> into a small bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> fish sauce</strong>, the<strong> remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a splash of <strong>water</strong></p><p>Stir it all together until the sugar has dissolved – this is your<strong> nuoc cham</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add your <strong>mooli slaw mix</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>nuoc cham </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled nuoc cham mooli slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked with a slight bite, drain the <strong>rice noodles</strong> and set aside</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lean pork patties are cooked through, add your<strong> pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [680ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min – this is your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>pork bun cha</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime[s]</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-lean-pork-bun-cha-rice-noodles/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked rice noodles</strong> in a bowl and top with the <strong>lean pork bun cha</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>remaining nuoc cham </strong>to the side and drizzle over</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli rounds</strong>, <strong>chopped mint </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Serve<strong> </strong>the <strong>quick-pickled nuoc cham mooli slaw </strong>to the side and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
